```

---

## 🧠 Implementation

### 1. **Haversine Formula**
The Haversine formula calculates the distance between two points on a sphere (Earth) given their longitudes and latitudes.

```perl
sub haversine {
    my ($lat1, $lon1, $lat2, $lon2) = @_;
    my $R = 6371; # Radius of Earth in kilometers

    my $dlat = deg2rad($lat2 - $lat1);
    my $dlon = deg2rad($lon2 - $lon1);

    my $a = sin($dlat/2)**2 + cos(deg2rad($lat1)) * cos(deg2rad($lat2)) * sin($dlon/2)**2;
    my $c = 2 * atan2(sqrt($a), sqrt(1 - $a));
    my $distance = $R * $c;

    return $distance;
}
```

### 2. **Degree to Radian Conversion**
```perl
sub deg2rad {
    my ($degrees) = @_;
    return $degrees * pi / 180;
}
```

